    {
      "id": "1288592084697223222",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2024-09-26T05:04:53.875+09:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "There's a lot going on with this card just for the fact that it extinguishes the current Ghostflame instead of preventing Advance at the end of your turn. You can still use it in Afterlife decks normally would before the update but there's a lot more tactical use to it now.\nYou can also just use this with <Xanatos Icy Charm> and go deep into Afterlife. The extra energy will allow you to save more Afterlife cards for later and to Retract more for the sake of <Into Shadow> or <Devil's Dance>.\nA cute thing you can do with this card is to activate it on the 5th Ghostflame (2nd Crushing) and have x4 draw Step Throughs for the rest of the combat.\n1. It no longer antisynergizes with Spirit Brand, so you don't lose Block that you would normally be getting, and you can still at least ignite one Ghostflame each turn to gain its effects.\n2. Extinguishing the Ghostflame allows you to reignite it, meaning you could stay on the Bolstering Ghostflame (or adjacent to it for the sake of <Forked Flame> and <Catch Up>) for tons of Block.\n3. It synergizes with <Soul Stone>, meaning if you use Afterlife to activate it, you can still Advance normally towards the Inferno, which is really cool.\n4. You can still cancel the debuff with Artifact or Orange Pellets, the power currently works like Biased Cognition where the buff and debuff are seperate.",
      "author": {
        "id": "370020173610090537",
