    {
      "id": "1288599220080607376",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2024-09-26T05:33:15.083+09:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Upgrade is handy to lower the tempo cost of casting this, usually worth pursuing if you are stuck on 3 energy of very energy hungry. Much better with runic pyramid so that you can camp on the bolster flame more easily. Pellets can cleanse the debuff, and clockwork souvenir can block it if you draw it quickly enough. Ice cream lets you float the extra energy over between turns for big plays when you find your card draw. Bottled tornado makes it much easier to build around the effect, and bolster rod and mummified hand lower the tempo cost. I think overall here and now is in a pretty good place among the hexaghost rares, offering the 4th energy when you need it, and with a drawback that can be played around in multiple ways.",
